Articles of agreement had, made, and concluded, between the commissioners of the Right Honorable the Lord Willoughby of Parham, of the one partie; and the commissioners of the Parliament of England, of the other partie: being in order to the rendition of the island of Barbadoes Treaties, etc. England and Wales, 1652-01-11. Barbados. Willoughby of Parham, Francis Willoughby, Baron, 1613?-1666. England and Wales.
[2], 9, [1] p.
[s.n.], London : Printed in the yeer, 1652.
The agreement, concluded 11 Jan. 1652, transfers control of the Island of Barbadoes to the Parliament. Annotation on Thomason copy: "may 10th". Reproduction of the original in the British Library.
